\newlabel{fig:horizon-sweep}{{9}{11}{\textbf {Horizon sensitivity.} Left: mean absolute Hurst estimation error $|\hat H - H|$ vs.\ horizon $T$. Right: IV RMSE at terminal maturity vs.\ $T$. Hurst error decreases monotonically with $T$ (more data $\Rightarrow $ better frequency resolution). IV RMSE is non-monotone: it stays low for $T\leq 2$~yr and spikes at $T=5$~yr, where the low-frequency singularity degrades the PSD fit}{figure.9}{}}
